entries.npc_dropoff_4: Mooie-mooie tanks! Heydo, Ebenn! Yousa sendin' mesa to be learnin' de Jedi mind tricks?
entries.npc_takeme_4: Issa true? My hearin' Baobab say mesa Force-sensitive? Is dat bein' right? Oyi, mooie-mooie! I luv yous! Yousa be takin' me to Baobab now.
entries.npc_breech_4: Heydo! Yousa sent from de Baobab guy?
entries.dontknowyou_4: My not knowin' what you want wit' mesa.
entries.otherescort_4: My not knowin' what you want wit' mesa.
entries.npc_failure_4: Wha? Who are you? What? You were doing a job for me? Bosh. Never saw you before in my life. Go away, I need a nap.
entries.npc_noloc_4: Good, good! Now, the coordinates you need are -- uh -- mmm. Mmmnhh. Hzznt -- hzzznt -- Uh? What? Who are you? Go away, let me sleep.
entries.npc_work_4: Hzzznt -- nuh? What? Are you back? You're finished with that job? No? Then don't bother me until you're done. I need my sleep.
entries.npc_reward_4: Wha? Who's this? Some kind of alien thing! Well, I'll have Rinto take care of this monster. Who are you, youngster? Do I owe you money? I remember now -- you brought me Rinto from the wilderness. Here, take a little something for your time.
entries.npc_backtowork_4: I'm tired of talking. I need a nap. You go on now, Master Jedi.
entries.npc_4_4: by undergoing the ceremonial Passage Rite at the semi-summer festival on Vintrus. Wait, was it Vintrus --? No, it wasn't the Passage Rite, it was -- well, maybe I don't remember. What about that job? Please don't keep an old man waiting, Master Jedi.
entries.npc_3_4: What? Can't do it? Well, stop wasting my time then. Very rude for a Jedi Knight to waste an old man's time!
entries.npc_2_4: Good. Pay the Jedi, Rinto. Rinto? Where is he? Well, Master, I'll pay you when you bring me your Jedi friend.
entries.npc_1_4: Ah? Oh, you're back. I remember you from the Clone Wars, don't I? Good. I have a favor to ask, Master Jedi. Don't lie to me, I saw you with that Jedi Knight, what's-his-name. He just called, asked me to send a guide to bring him here for a nice dinner. Won't that be nice? What do you say, Master Jedi?
entries.player_sorry_3: I'll keep working on the mission.
entries.player_reset_3: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.notit_3: I was expecting the -- well, a document from Ebenn. This isn't it.
entries.gotowork_3: I was expecting the -- well, a document from Ebenn. Didn't you bring it?
entries.npc_smuggle_3: At last! The plans for the Emperor's Retreat! Princess Leia will be glad to see these. Thanks!
entries.npc_breech_3: Hello! Did Ebenn send the plans?
entries.dontknowyou_3: I don't think you're the one I'm supposed to meet.
entries.otherescort_3: I don't think you're the one I'm supposed to meet.
entries.npc_failure_3: Didn't deliver that poetry? Bosh, I could do it myself, and I'm a lot older than you, youngster. Well, I'll find someone else. Yes I will! Hah!
entries.npc_noloc_3: Good, good! Now, the coordinates you need are -- uh -- mmm. Mmmnhh. Hzznt -- hzzznt -- Uh? What? Who are you? Go away, let me sleep.
entries.npc_work_3: Hzzznt -- nuh? What? Are you back? You're finished with that job? No? Then don't bother me until you're done. I need my sleep.
entries.npc_reward_3: Wha? Who are you? What's that? Plans? I don't know anything about any plans. Oh, I remember. I sent you off with that junk poetry. Here, take a little something for your time. Spend it while you can, I say.
entries.npc_backtowork_3: I'm tired of talking. I need a nap. You go on now.
entries.npc_4_3: Me? I'm, I'm -- I forget how old. When was the Trade Federation War? I retired not long after that. Retired to Manda with my wife, Pookie, and we had a miniature bantha named Nuke. Good old Nuke. I never should have outlived them. But here I am. Now, what about that job?
entries.npc_3_3: What? Can't do it? Well, stop wasting my time then. Haven't got that much time left.
entries.npc_2_3: Good, good -- What? You still here? Go, go! You're looking for that poet -- what's her name -- Nura Tinall. As if I would ever read her poetry, hah! That's what I say, Hah!
entries.npc_1_3: Wait -- what year is this? This is now, isn't it? I thought so. I drift away sometimes. Well, want another job, youngster? Some fool of a poet -- young sprat! -- sent me her poems to recommend to my publishers. Hah! Can't fool an old man! She just wants me to recommend this junk to my publisher! I mean -- uh -- I forget what I meant. Anyway. Take her junk poetry back to her without my recommendation. That'll show her!
entries.player_sorry_2: I'll keep working on the mission.
entries.player_reset_2: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.notit_2: I was expecting a payment from that old man. This isn't it.
entries.gotowork_2: I was expecting a payment from that old man. Didn't you bring it?
entries.npc_smuggle_2: About time. I told that old man those medical supplies wouldn't budge past the Imperial blockades until I got this money. Okay, I'm off to the Outer Rim.
entries.npc_breech_2: Hey! Did that old man send the money?
entries.npc_failure_2: What? You say I sent you to deliver funds to Chancellor Valorum? That's ridiculous! Valorum hasn't been around since the Old Republic! Go away, let me sleep.
entries.npc_noloc_2: Good, good! Now, the coordinates you need are -- uh -- mmm. Mmmnhh. Hzznt -- hzzznt -- Uh? What? Who are you? Go away, let me sleep.
entries.npc_work_2: Hzzznt -- nuh? What? Are you back? You're finished with that job? No? Then don't bother me until you're done. I need my sleep.
entries.npc_reward_2: All right then. Here's your pay. That Chancellor Valorum had better buckle down, or the whole Republic will in trouble. Yes, yes -- Wait, who are you? Looking for a job?
entries.npc_backtowork_2: I'm tired of talking. I need a nap. You go on now.
entries.npc_4_2: Wha? Me? Oh, I'm just an old man. Used to be on the Royal Council. Traveled, wrote a lot of books. The Galactic Phrasebook, that was mine. Collected folk art of the Hutts -- very interesting, Hutt art, I remember one piece that -- Well, never mind. I need these funds delivered, youngster. What do you say?
entries.npc_3_2: What? Can't do it? Well, stop wasting my time then. Haven't got that much time left.
entries.npc_2_2: All right, that's the kind of vim I used to have myself, eighty or ninety years ago! Take this to -- oh, what's his name? Name, name -- Tanner Helton! Go. Hope I'm still alive when you get back.
entries.npc_1_2: All right, I can hear you now, you don't have to shout -- Where am I? Oh yes. You're looking for a job, right? Well, listen: The Republic is falling on hard times, and unless we do something to help Chancellor Valorum, that Pala-- Plapa -- that Senator What's-his-name will bring ruin on us all. Deliver these funds to set up a commission inquiring into what may be done.
entries.player_sorry_1: I'll keep working on the mission.
entries.player_reset_1: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.npc_dropoff_1: Thanks for the escort. You'll be able to talk to Ebenn now. -- Hello, Great-Grandpa! It's Rinto! I'm here to fix your ears!
entries.npc_takeme_1: Ebenn sent you, I assume? I met the sympathizer and got the Imperial political data. Oh, aren't you --? Okay. I don't blame you for being confused -- Ebenn can be crotchety sometimes. He was once a great man, though, long ago.
entries.npc_breech_1: Hello! I'm Rinto Liprus! Did Ebenn send you?
entries.dontknowyou_1: I think you're looking for someone else.
entries.otherescort_1: I think you're looking for someone else.
entries.npc_failure_1: What? I can't hear you. Where is that assistant? Rinto! Rinto!
entries.npc_noloc_1: What? I need my assistant, Rinto Liprus. I sent him to -- darnit, where did he go? I forget. You come back later, I'll remember, you'll see.
entries.npc_work_1: Hzzznt -- nuh? What? Are you back? You're finished with that job? No? Then don't bother me until you're done. I need my sleep.
entries.npc_reward_1: Ah, here's Rinto, and here's my ears. Ah, that's better. I can hear now. Take a little something for your time, youngster. Now, what brings you here? Looking for a job, are you?
entries.npc_backtowork_1: What? I can't hear you. Go find my assistant.
entries.npc_4_1: Speak up, I can't hear a thing. You need to find my assistant. His name's Rinto Liprus. My great-grandson, I think. Will you go find him?
entries.npc_3_1: What? I can't hear you. Where's my assistant? He'll fix my ears.
entries.npc_2_1: What? I can't hear you. Go find my assistant, Rinto Liprus. I sent him -- where did I send him -- oh! Into the wilderness. Now why did I do that?
entries.npc_1_1: Hzznt -- wha? What's that? I was sleeping. Oh. You. You're the one they sent looking for a job. Right? Speak up, I can't hear you. They made me get one of those ear implants, but the thing makes my skull buzz. Where's my assistant? He can fix my ears. Bring me my assistant. I sent him out somewhere. I forget why.
entries.npc_reset_1: Hzznt -- uh? What? Can't do the job? You woke me up to say you can't do my job? Well, come on back when you can do it, then.
entries.cantwork: Hzznt -- ah? Uh? Sorry, I was sleeping. You're the one they sent to do that job? What's that? Busy, you say? Well, come back later, then.
